<div id="bookReviews">
  




  <div class="friendReviews elementListBrown" >
    <div class="section firstReview">
      

<div id="review_4058114789" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4058114789" />
    <a title="Grady" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1362506-grady"><img alt="Grady" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1442472304p2/1362506.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4058114789?book_show_action=true">Jun 14, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Grady" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Grady" href="/user/show/1362506-grady">Grady</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4058114789" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15795879777591925428">‘Our surroundings appeared as alluring as an inflamed pox sore’ – History, another view<br/><br/>Author Harry F MacDonald is a mystery – an author with no biographical information either on this site, within the book, or throughout the Internet. Possibilities – the name is a nom de plume for an established author of other genres, or a very private person who enjoys anonymity! <br/><br/>Approaching the life of an historic personage and shining a different light on the place and events and cast of characters encounte</span>
  <span id="freeText15795879777591925428" style="display:none">‘Our surroundings appeared as alluring as an inflamed pox sore’ – History, another view<br /><br />Author Harry F MacDonald is a mystery – an author with no biographical information either on this site, within the book, or throughout the Internet. Possibilities – the name is a nom de plume for an established author of other genres, or a very private person who enjoys anonymity! <br /><br />Approaching the life of an historic personage and shining a different light on the place and events and cast of characters encountered is a nod to both history and satire. MacDonald is not only a gifted composer of words; he/she/they is also a fine historian who has the power to convince us of vagaries of the chosen character – Casanova.<br /><br />The entertainment and appreciation of history is apparent in the ‘Advance Praise’ sector that opens the book – with hilarious raves and comments from the likes of Mozart, Marie-Antoinette, Benjamin Franklin, and Hellcat Brown: ‘Casanova proves once again that good girls go to heaven and bad girls go everywhere.’ Following that entre, the author offers a version of history – ‘History records that Casanova completed the twelve volumes of his memoirs and settled in Castle Dux in Bohemia to live out his senior years in a disgraceful and largely undeserved style. It was only with the discovery of this second account of those years that we need to reappraise his more mature years. The account, written by his later valet Jacques del Russo, recounts the intrigues and dalliances that occurred in the time just preceding the French revolution…1787 – 1793.’<br /><br />What follows is one of the more entertaining books imaginable - one that tackles historical figures in their interaction with the most famous womanizer in history. In placing well known figures in context with the fol de rol of Casanova’s dalliances, the author provides some of the more sophisticated revisits to the global populace of the time, enfolding affairs and dramas that are sensationally entertaining. <br /><br />As apropos to the lifestyle of the titular character, the writing is a bit naughty at times, but the atmosphere created is thoroughly enjoyable. This is one of those books to keep around and to read when the world outside feels incompatible – a dollop of spicy sugar to put life’s madness in perspective! Highly recommended.<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="15795879777591925428" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

