        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4052712453" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2248056767350899891">Casanova and the Devil&apos;s Doorbell by Harry F. MacDonald is written as a historical piece on the famous Giacomo Casanova. This tale follows Casanova in his later years, as penned by his valet, Jacques del Rosso. Jacques was a young man learning the ways of an adventurer under the tutorship of Casanova. His dallies with the ladies are legendary, but there was much more to the man as he traveled between countries. His connections and information played an impressive role in the political world at t</span>
  <span id="freeText2248056767350899891" style="display:none">Casanova and the Devil's Doorbell by Harry F. MacDonald is written as a historical piece on the famous Giacomo Casanova. This tale follows Casanova in his later years, as penned by his valet, Jacques del Rosso. Jacques was a young man learning the ways of an adventurer under the tutorship of Casanova. His dallies with the ladies are legendary, but there was much more to the man as he traveled between countries. His connections and information played an impressive role in the political world at that time. His knowledge was often sought by royalty to ensure their lineage continues.<br /><br />The author of Casanova and the Devil's Doorbell is a mystery and creates an allusion of what kind of person would write a book as witty and erotic as this one. The story added twists as Casanova associated with many different types of people. </span>
  <a data-text-id="2248056767350899891" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
