        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4059758712" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6096326718553336272">Casanova and the Devil&apos;s Doorbell by Harry F. MacDonald is a witty take on the historical figure of Casanova. Combining satire with history makes this a fun tale recounted by Casanova&apos;s scribe and valet, Jacques del Rosso. The story begins appropriately with a journey, as Casanova teaches Jacques the ways of the world and women. Full of accurate historical detail along with biting satire, this is a fun romp of a book. This is a thoroughly enjoyable read that is both entertaining and unbelievably</span>
  <span id="freeText6096326718553336272" style="display:none">Casanova and the Devil's Doorbell by Harry F. MacDonald is a witty take on the historical figure of Casanova. Combining satire with history makes this a fun tale recounted by Casanova's scribe and valet, Jacques del Rosso. The story begins appropriately with a journey, as Casanova teaches Jacques the ways of the world and women. Full of accurate historical detail along with biting satire, this is a fun romp of a book. This is a thoroughly enjoyable read that is both entertaining and unbelievably educational as you learn more about the life and times of Casanova. You will gain an understanding of eighteenth-century Europe as well, all while being taken down the path of ill repute. Wild and totally inappropriate, this story is highly recommended. </span>
  <a data-text-id="6096326718553336272" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

