<div id="review_4135509028" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4135509028" />
    <a title="Emerson" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/4243343-emerson"><img alt="Emerson" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1603391146p2/4243343.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4135509028?book_show_action=true">Jul 25, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Emerson" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Emerson" href="/user/show/4243343-emerson">Emerson</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4135509028" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4329667121160546175">The marvelous adventures of Casanova are not over yet. In his book Casanova and the Devil&apos;s Doorbell, Harry F. MacDonald explores the later years of the infamous rogue Casanova. The story is told from the perspective of Casanova’s valet Jacques del Rosso who remained with him after the completion of Casanova’s own memoirs. The reader sees the accounts of the disgraced Casanova in his later years where he still managed to cause trouble. As someone who is fascinated with the Casanova story, I love</span>
  <span id="freeText4329667121160546175" style="display:none">The marvelous adventures of Casanova are not over yet. In his book Casanova and the Devil's Doorbell, Harry F. MacDonald explores the later years of the infamous rogue Casanova. The story is told from the perspective of Casanova’s valet Jacques del Rosso who remained with him after the completion of Casanova’s own memoirs. The reader sees the accounts of the disgraced Casanova in his later years where he still managed to cause trouble. As someone who is fascinated with the Casanova story, I loved getting to read more of the spectacular tale. The book is humorous and risqué while also making it easy to engage with the historic aspects of the story. It is a wild ride from beginning to end which I would highly recommend embarking upon. </span>
  <a data-text-id="4329667121160546175" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


