<div id="review_4152331873" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4152331873" />
    <a title="Silver Duck" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/138480442-silver-duck"><img alt="Silver Duck" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1628005286p2/138480442.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4152331873?book_show_action=true">Aug 03, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Silver Duck" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Silver Duck" href="/user/show/138480442-silver-duck">Silver Duck</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4152331873" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10047843348116692770">This tale follows Casanova in his later years, an interesting and absorbing narrative of Casanova’s life as an elderly gentleman who is still full of pep and still able to seduce the ladies! Giacomo Casanova passes his knowledge and skills to his valet Jacques del Rosso, teaching him the ways of the world and loose women as he sees it. (disgracefully and full of mischief!) Jaques, although reluctant to learn in the beginning, eventually succumbs to Casanova’s charisma!<br/><br/><br/>Completely appropriate to C</span>
  <span id="freeText10047843348116692770" style="display:none">This tale follows Casanova in his later years, an interesting and absorbing narrative of Casanova’s life as an elderly gentleman who is still full of pep and still able to seduce the ladies! Giacomo Casanova passes his knowledge and skills to his valet Jacques del Rosso, teaching him the ways of the world and loose women as he sees it. (disgracefully and full of mischief!) Jaques, although reluctant to learn in the beginning, eventually succumbs to Casanova’s charisma!<br /><br /><br />Completely appropriate to Casanova’s character, the writing is witty, erotic and completely absorbing. I also have to admit that I found the book to be quite educational as I learned many things I knew nothing about. Very glad I found this.<br />A book to read when there’s no one around to disturb you! Highly recommended</span>
