  <span id="freeText8993622895556006157" style="display:none">Jacques del Rosso was Giacomo Casanova's scribe and valet, and in this fun and intriguing tale Cassanova teaches him everything there is to know about life and his charlatan ways.<br /><br />Despite this book being a work of fiction, it provided me an illuminative insight into some aspects of life in the time of the great Casanova. Very interesting stuff.<br /><br />Combining wit with history Author Harry F MacDonald made this a fun and exciting read. I highly recommend it, but as the the book blurb advises this is not for those who are faint- hearted or for those who are set on judging works and men by modern day standards of political correctness, haha.</span>
