<span id="freeTextContainer10470136958568754313">Witty and creepy, Casanova and the Devil’s Doorbell is an intriguing read. It’s like a “gentleman’s” guidebook mixed with fantasy. Most of the book is dialog between Casanova and his young servant Jacques as they meet people, flirt with women, and travel the countryside. Set near the time of the French Revolution, you also get a bit of culture and history mixed in. <br/><br/>I recommend it for any guys or gals who want to read something a little risqué without going over the line. It will especially fit y</span>
  <span id="freeText10470136958568754313" style="display:none">Witty and creepy, Casanova and the Devil’s Doorbell is an intriguing read. It’s like a “gentleman’s” guidebook mixed with fantasy. Most of the book is dialog between Casanova and his young servant Jacques as they meet people, flirt with women, and travel the countryside. Set near the time of the French Revolution, you also get a bit of culture and history mixed in. <br /><br />I recommend it for any guys or gals who want to read something a little risqué without going over the line. It will especially fit your style if you’re into magic and the supernatural as well. </span>
